<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="491" pageId="15" pageNumber="490" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1874,2007]" box="[199,1179,1910,1935]" pageId="15" pageNumber="490">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,1017,1910,1935]" pageId="15" pageNumber="490">Recorded damage and economic importance in the orchards of Iran:</emphasis>
Not recorded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1874,2007]" pageId="15" pageNumber="490">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,953,1946,1971]" pageId="15" pageNumber="490">Recorded damage in the orchards of other parts of the world:</emphasis>
Tested positive for Aster yellows (AY) in vineyards in Europe (
<bibRefCitation box="[391,633,1982,2007]" pageId="15" pageNumber="490" refId="ref21144" refString="Orenstein, S., Zahavi, T., Nestle, D., Shardon, R., Barkalifa, M. &amp; Weintraub, P. G. (2003) Spatial dispersion patterns of potential leafhopper and planthopper (Homoptera) vectors of phytoplasma in wine vineyards. Annals of Applied Biology, 142 (3), 341 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1744 - 7348.2003. tb 00259. x" type="journal article">
Orenstein 
<emphasis box="[508,558,1982,2007]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="490">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[199,1156,151,213]" box="[199,1156,151,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,562,151,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="491">Recorded distribution in Iran:</emphasis>
Generally distributed (
<bibRefCitation box="[820,1144,151,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="491" refId="ref20841" refString="Mozaffarian, F. &amp; Wilson, M. R. (2016) A checklist of the leafhoppers of Iran (Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Cicadellidae). Zootaxa, 4062 (1), 1 - 63. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4062.1.1" type="journal article">Mozaffarian &amp; Wilson 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[199,1156,151,213]" box="[199,1014,188,213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,342,188,213]" pageId="16" pageNumber="491">Conclusion:</emphasis>
The vector status of this species in Iran needs further study.
</paragraph>
